The Software acts as a client interface to third-party Large Language Model (LLM) providers. You are solely responsible for obtaining, securing, and paying for access to these third-party services (e.g., OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini) via your own API keys.

4. TELEMETRY AND DATA
The Software requires an active license key generated via backbencher.cc. The Software may periodically connect to Backbencher servers to validate license status (with a 7-day offline grace period). Your source code and prompts are processed locally or sent directly to your configured LLM provider; Backbencher does not collect your proprietary source code.

